s in the upper echelon of K Street practitioners? Van Scoyoc Associates Inc.=
 does it by signing up a stable of smaller clients and working hard to retai=
n them. Quinn Gillespie & Associates doesn't have a long client list, but it=
 is at the top of the heap in terms of average fee per client. Greenberg Tra=
urig, meanwhile, lured away a rival firm's top rainmaker-and his lucrative b=
ook of clients.=20
